                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_ærttīvyn" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ærttīvyn</orth><form type="participle"><orth>ærttyvd</orth></form></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>ærttevun</orth><form type="participle"><orth>ærttivd</orth></form></form><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>блестеть</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>to glitter</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>блистать </q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>to be radiant with</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>сверкать</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>to sparkle</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>сиять</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>to radiate</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>светиться</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>to shine</q></tr></sense></sense><re xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/><form type="lemma"><orth>ærttevagæ</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>молния</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>lightning</q></tr></sense><note>(<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MD"/><biblScope>1940 III 60</biblScope></bibl>)</note></re><exampleGrp><example><quote>ærttīvy syǧzærīnaw</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>блестит как золото</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>it is shining loke gold</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>101</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>jæ xūd ærfældæxta je ʽrttīvag cæstytyl</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>надвинул шапку на свои сверкающие глаза</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>[he] pulled his hat over his sparkling eyes</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Æfx._Xæs."/><biblScope>103</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>komæj zyng ferttyvta</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>из ущелья сверкнул огонь</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>fire flashed from the gorge</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>194</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>stur ajdænæ ærttevæntæ kodta xormæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>большое зеркало блестело на солнце</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>a big mirror was sparkling in the sun</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>119</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>bajrægutæ ærttevæntæ kaluncæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>жеребята сверкают (чистотой)</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>foals are spotlessly clean</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_SD"/><biblScope>271%l4%l</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><exampleGrp><example><quote>ærttīvy syǧzærīnaw</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>блестит как золото</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>it is shining loke gold</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>101</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>jæ xūd ærfældæxta je ʽrttīvag cæstytyl</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>надвинул шапку на свои сверкающие глаза</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>[he] pulled his hat over his sparkling eyes</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Æfx._Xæs."/><biblScope>103</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>komæj zyng ferttyvta</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>из ущелья сверкнул огонь</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>fire flashed from the gorge</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>194</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>stur ajdænæ ærttevæntæ kodta xormæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>большое зеркало блестело на солнце</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>a big mirror was sparkling in the sun</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>119</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>bajrægutæ ærttevæntæ kaluncæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>жеребята сверкают (чистотой)</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>foals are spotlessly clean</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_SD"/><biblScope>271%l4%l</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Вместе с <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>*ardēp-(ʽrdʽур)</w> <gloss><q>блистать</q></gloss></mentioned> представляет, по-видимому, сложение из *%iāϑr-dīp%i-, буквально „огне-блистать“; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>ātr-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>ʽʽtr</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/> <w>art</w> <gloss><q>огонь</q></gloss></mentioned>. Во второй части не %itap%i-, как думает <bibl><author>Reichelt</author></bibl>, а %idīp%i-, ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>dīp-</w> <gloss><q>пылать</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘сверкать’, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/> <w>dif-: dift-</w> <gloss><q>загораться</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘зажигаться’. <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>*ardēpāk(ʽrtʽypʽk)</w> <gloss><q>сияние</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘сияющий’= <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/> <w>ærttevag</w></mentioned> (%i*rōxšn ardēpāk%i = %iroxs ærttevag%i „свет сияющий“). Если согдийское %iʽrδʽyp-%i возводить к %i*drafaya-%i (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Gershevitch"/><biblScope>§ 439</biblScope></bibl>), то осетинское слово придется отделить от согдийского, так как %iærttev%i- (с %itt%i!) фонетически никак не может восходить к *%idrafaya%i.%n<bibl><author>Reichelt</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ZII"/><biblScope>IV 247</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><author>Benveniste</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_TSP"/><biblScope>235</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Together with <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>*ardēp-(ʽrdʽур)</w> <gloss><q>to shine</q></gloss></mentioned> the word of interest represents apparently the composition of %i*āϑr%i-%idīp%i-, which literally means ‘to fire-shine’, compare <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>ātr-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>ʽʽtr</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/> <w>art</w> <gloss><q>fire</q></gloss></mentioned>. It is not %itap%i- in the second part as <bibl><author>Reichelt</author></bibl>supposes, but %idīp%i-, compare <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>dīp-</w> <gloss><q>to blaze</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘to sparkle’, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/> <w>dif-: dift-</w> <gloss><q>to blaze up</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘to light up’. <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>*ardēpāk(ʽrtʽypʽk)</w> <gloss><q>radiance</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘radiant’= <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/> <w>ærttevag</w></mentioned> (%i*rōxšn ardēpāk%i = %iroxs ærttevag%i 'shining light'). If one traces Sogdian %iʽrδʽyp-%i back to %i*drafaya-%i (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Gershevitch"/><biblScope>§ 439</biblScope></bibl>), then the Ossetic word has to be separated from the Sogdian one because %iærttev%i- (with %itt%i!) cannot trace back to *%idrafaya%i phonetically.%n<bibl><author>Reichelt</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ZII"/><biblScope>IV 247</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><author>Benveniste</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_TSP"/><biblScope>235</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>